This paper is focused on the detection of zero-day attacks and vulnerabilities using machine learning algorithms. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the category of Computer Security and Cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper investigates the performance of different machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of accurate detection of zero-day malware for network administrators, which could place it in the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the detection of malware in network systems, which could also place it in the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
